body:
I was [comparing Yosys against ISE and Vivado](https://github.com/rodrigomelo9/yosys-versus), using examples provided by Xilinx. I found a problem instantiating the LUT2 primitive in 2 of 3 cases.

To check with iverilog and for the generic `synth` command, I used the following blackbox definition (`blackboxes.v`) and it works:
```
(* blackbox *)
module LUT2 (O, I0, I1);
    parameter [3:0] INIT = 4'h0;
    output O;
    input I0;
    input I1;
endmodule
```

I have three examples from Xilinx:
* primitive_1.v
```
module v_primitive_1 (I0,I1,O);
    input I0,I1;
    output O;

    (* INIT="1" *)
	 LUT2 inst (.I0(I0), .I1(I1), .O(O));

endmodule
```
* primitive_2.v:
```
module v_primitive_2 (I0,I1,O);
    input I0,I1;
    output O;

    LUT2 #(4'h1) inst (.I0(I0), .I1(I1), .O(O));

endmodule
```
* primitive_3.v:
```
module v_primitive_3 (I0,I1,O);
    input I0,I1;
    output O;

    LUT2 inst (.I0(I0), .I1(I1), .O(O));
    defparam inst.INIT = 4'h1;

endmodule
```

The cases `primitive_1.v` and `primitive_2.v` fail:
```
$ yosys -Q -p "read_verilog primitive_1.v; synth_xilinx -top v_primitive_1"
...
3.47.4. Continuing TECHMAP pass.
No more expansions possible.

3.48. Executing XILINX_DFFOPT pass (optimize FF control signal usage).
Optimizing FFs in v_primitive_1.
terminate called after throwing an instance of 'std::out_of_range'
  what():  dict::at()
Aborted
```

> **Note:** the file `primitive_1.v` has as description *The INIT value is specified with an attribute, which is rejected by XST*

